{{Quote|Zaril travelled to Tatooine&hellip; meeting with the ''B'omarr monks''&hellip; members of a mysterious cult that removed their own ''brains'' so they could contemplate the mysteries of the universe without the distraction of a ''physical body''.|[[Thom Hudd]]|<ref name="RTVC 4">[[Star Wars Adventures: Return to Vader's Castle 4|''Star Wars Adventures: Return to Vader's Castle'' 4]]</ref>}}
The '''B'omarr Order''',<ref name="USW">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> which consisted of '''B'omarr monks''', was a religious order that believed in isolating themselves from all physical sensation to enhance the power of their minds. To that aim, enlightened [[monk]]s had their [[brain]]s transplanted into nutrient-filled jars.<ref name="RotJ paperback novel">[[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (paperback novel)|''Star Wars: Return of the Jedi'' junior novelization]]</ref> Whenever they wanted to move, those bottled-brains used [[spider]]-like [[droid]] [[Brain walker|walkers]].<ref name="AE" /> Older monks used four-[[Limb|legged]] walkers, but younger monks used a six-legged variant.<ref name="CE:UaE">''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia: Updated and Expanded]]''</ref>

The order possessed multiple regeneration gems, which at the time of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure|Jabba the Hutt]] were stored underground behind triple doors.<ref name="CL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|This looks like one of those B'omarr monk monasteries that I read about in my studies at the Temple.|[[Ahsoka Tano]]|<ref name="TCW" />}}
[[File:BomarrMonk-SWCT.png|thumb|300px|left|A B'omarr monk moves through Jabba's palace.]]
The order built monasteries in [[the galaxy]], including a [[B'omarr Order Monastery|monastery]] on the [[jungle]] [[Planet|world]] of [[Teth]] in [[Wild Space]]. Some of their temples were taken over by [[smuggler]]s, who turned them into their personal retreats.<ref name="TCW" /> The B'omarr monks were also present on [[Tatooine]],<ref name="AE" /> but Jabba the [[Hutt]] assumed control of their monastery, turning it into his personal [[Boba Fett's Palace|palace]].<ref name="BtPotDS">''[[Return of the Jedi: Beware the Power of the Dark Side!]]''</ref> Despite that, Jabba allowed the monks to still roam around his appropriated palace, as he enjoyed the gruesome sight of them.<ref name="CE:UaE" />

At some point, Jabba's cousin [[Crakka]] attempted to steal the brain of the thief [[Zaril]] from the B'omarr Order's Catacombs where the other living brains of the Order were being held. During the attempt, Crakka was detected by the Order, incurring their wrath. As Crakka made her escape, [[Salacious B. Crumb]] interrupted her, causing her to drop the brain. When confronted by Jabba, Crakka attempted to offer the secret's of Zaril's brain but the brain had already been severely damaged by the drop to yield any secrets. Seeing no use in the brain and still angered by Crakka's betrayal, Jabba did not hesitate to let the Order take their vengeance on Crakka and add her brain amongst the Order's current collection of bottled brains in the Catacombs.<ref name="RTVC 4" />

In [[4 ABY]], B'omarr monks were present at Jabba's Palace when [[Jedi Knight]] [[Luke Skywalker]] came to [[Rescue of Han Solo|rescue]] the [[Corellian]] smuggler [[Han Solo]] from captivity.<ref name="RotJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref> Shortly after Jabba's [[death]], the monks took over the palace and allowed the [[Whiphid]] [[bounty hunter]] [[J'Quille]] to join them after he found himself unable to leave the planet.<ref name="CE:UaE" /> By [[9 ABY]],<ref name="Date">{{MandoDate|16}}</ref> [[Bib Fortuna]] had taken over the palace before he was [[Attack on Jabba's Palace (Boba Fett)|killed]] by [[Boba Fett]].<ref name="TM-C16">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 16: The Rescue}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The B'omarr Order first appeared in the [[1983]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], in the form of brains attached to spider droids.<ref name="RotJ" /> The droids were based upon sketches by the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[original trilogy]] concept designer [[Ralph McQuarrie]], which later appeared in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] [[1995]] book ''[[The Illustrated Star Wars Universe]]'', where the [[B'omarr Order/Legends|B'omarr]] were originally identified.<ref name="TISWU">''[[The Illustrated Star Wars Universe]]''</ref> They were later identified in the [[2015]] reference book ''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''.<ref name="USW" />

